heatPlot

Source: R/heatPlot.R
heatPlot.Rd

The heatPlot function generates a dot-based heatmap to visualize correlations between genes and enriched pathways from Gene Set Enrichment Analysis (GSEA) results. Each dot represents a gene–pathway relationship, colored by the correlation coefficient (or log2 fold change) and sized by statistical significance measures such as p-value or adjusted p-value.

Usage

heatPlot(
  seDataFgsea,
  breaklineN = 30,
  showCategory = 5,
  size = "pvalue",
  color = "cor",
  disFun = "euclidean",
  hclustFun = "ward.D",
  fontSize = 8
)

Arguments

seDataFgsea

A SummarizedExperiment object containing GSEA results and correlation data. Typically extracted using the internal .extractDF() function with types "gseaReadable" and "corCoef".

breaklineN

Integer. Number of characters after which pathway names are line-broken for readability. Default is 30.

showCategory

Either a numeric value indicating the number of top pathways to display, or a character vector specifying particular pathway names to include. Default is 5.

size

Character. Column name representing statistical significance values for dot sizing. Must be one of "pvalue" or "p.adjust". Default is "pvalue".

color

Character. Column name representing the color variable for dots. Must be one of "cor" or "log2FC". Default is "cor".

disFun

Character. Distance metric for gene clustering along the x-axis, passed to dist(). Supported options include "euclidean", "manhattan", "canberra", etc. Default is "euclidean".

hclustFun

Character. Hierarchical clustering method used for gene ordering, passed to hclust(). Must be one of "ward.D", "ward.D2", "average", "complete", "single", etc. Default is "ward.D".

fontSize

Numeric. Base font size for axis labels and legends. Default is 8.

Value

A named list with two elements:

heatPlot

A ggplot2 object showing the gene–pathway heatmap with correlation color and significance size encoding.

tableHeatPlot

A data.frame summarizing the data used in the plot, including:

  • original_name: Original pathway IDs

  • label_name: Formatted pathway names with line breaks

  • Gene: Gene symbols

  • Coefficient: Correlation coefficient or log2FC values (depending on the color parameter)

  • Statistical significance column: The column specified by the size parameter (pvalue or p.adjust)

  • neg_log_size: Transformed significance value (-log10 of the size column)

Details

This function provides a compact visualization to highlight how individual genes contribute to enriched pathways. The heatmap layout displays genes on the x-axis (optionally clustered by correlation patterns) and pathways on the y-axis. Dot color represents correlation direction/intensity, and dot size encodes statistical significance.

Visual encoding follows the SigFun aesthetic design:

  • Dot color: Correlation coefficient (cor) or log2FC

  • Dot size: -log10(p-value) or -log10(p.adjust)

  • X-axis: Genes clustered by correlation similarity

  • Y-axis: Pathway names (wrapped by breaklineN)

Note

Requires ggplot2 (>= 3.5.0) and dplyr (>= 1.1.0) for full compatibility.
